386→                        <div id="content">Let $a\geq 1$. Must there exist some $b&#62;a$ such that\[\sum_{a\leq n\leq b}\frac{1}{n}=\frac{r_1}{s_1}\textrm{ and }\sum_{a\leq n\leq b+1}\frac{1}{n}=\frac{r_2}{s_2},\]with $(r_i,s_i)=1$ and $s_2&#60;s_1$? If so, how does this $b(a)$ grow with $a$?</div>
387→                        <div id="problem_id"><a href="/290">#290</a>: <a href="#cite-ErGr80-290" onclick="event.preventDefault();addNewBox('ErGr80','290'); return false;">[ErGr80,p.34]</a></div>
